## Bug B — `ReplayDivergenceError` leaks as traceback / exit 1 instead of EXIT_DIVERGENCE (5)

Same repro as Bug A. `cli/main.py::cmd_replay` (lines 411–422) catches only
`FileNotFoundError` and `sqlite3.OperationalError`. `EXIT_DIVERGENCE = 5` is
defined and documented in the module docstring (lines 10–16) but is never
returned from `replay`. The newly-mintable `fork.override.applied` divergence
path makes this newly reachable in normal usage.

### Fix sketch

```python
from activegraph.runtime.errors import ReplayDivergenceError
try:
    rt = Runtime.load(url, run_id=run_id)
except ReplayDivergenceError as e:
    click.echo(str(e), err=True)
    raise SystemExit(EXIT_DIVERGENCE)
```

