## Net call

Tests pass against the schema the tests defined. The implementation has
narrow correctness around DiligenceSettings-shape packs and is hostile to:

- multi-set on the same key in one invocation (Bug A, ship-blocker IMO)
- divergence exit code (Bug B, contract drift from cli/main.py docstring)
- packs with required fields (Bug C, blocks future packs)
- packs with non-primitive Pydantic types (Bug D, same)

Bugs A and B are exploitable today on the DiligenceSettings pack with no
new code. C and D are landmines that detonate the next time someone
introduces a pack with a more interesting schema.

Recommend Code Owner address A and B before declaring T3 closed; C and D
can be follow-up if scope-bounded, but they belong in CONTRACT amendments
either way so the next pack author knows the contract surface.
